            </p>
            <p >What is missing is a slight exposure and training in the form of a users manual to operate this wonderful machine known as human being. All animals have 5 senses, including human beings. Human beings have two additional attributes which separate us from rest of the animal kingdom, we have memory and imagination, both of which we have ended up misusing. Our mind is nothing but a thought generating gadget. With the lack of knowledge on how to use our mind. We end up using memories to fill us with a over dose of recollections / memories of all the past wrongs that the world and close associates and relatives have done to us. The other attribute called imagination, we are over working by constantly weaving horror stories, a quick look will reconfirm that almost none of our past horror stories have ever seen the light of the day. 
            </p>
            <p >
