            </p>
            <p >At Osgan Peace Foundation, our aim is to create consciousness about life is beyond, the I, me, myself, and without the other, life is meaningless, we are children of God and have the brains to comprehend that there is adequate on this planet for everybody’s need . let us get the greed out of us. As John Ruskin, author of the book, “unto this last, which inspired Mahatma Gandhi, to write and life by the book called “ Sarvodaya”, focussed to build a socially responsible self sustainable micro economy based culture, with larger focus on rural areas, to ease the ghettoisation, if a may use the word loosely for the constantly growing slums, in the cities, in order to cut cost and find cheap workmen. </p>
            <p >Today knowing that nearly almost a billion people are struggling for One square meal a day. The United Nations data, says, quote, “ Today, some 821 million people suffer chronically from hunger.</p>
