            <h2><a  >The Story of an ‘Idea’ and its ‘Journey ’</a></h2>
            
            <p>While serving at UNAVEM and subsequently in MONUA, in Angola in the year 1996 – 1997, one of the founder-member had a series of discussions with the other armed forces veterans from almost 36 countries of the world on whose war and peace for whom, this was followed by several discussions with socially responsible people from many a Non Governmental organizations, with chequered profiles of tireless, selfless services, for decades in adverse or rather hostile environments obtaining in or out of conflict zones,   the civil society on the need to spreading awareness on peace.  </p>
            <p>The idea of starting a peoples movement, world over took birth from these concerns and talks, wherein it was concluded that only with the active participation  and understanding in grown from grass root desire of the affected people to end conflict through non violent means. This would need a series of social and cultural exchanges lead by both “the affected” and the “not directly affected” segments of the people from the cross section of the world populace.  </p>
            <p>And Osgan Peace Foundation stands firmly committed to ensuring that this movement is exemplary in practice of people standing shoulder to shoulder with the adversaries and not let or get manipulated by ever growing breed of megalomaniacs and fanatics, who two often a part of the larger conspiracies of the collective  or isolated vested interests.  </p>
            <p>It is only the common man who faces the brunt. This lead to the “HOW” which resulted in Osgan Peace Foundation becoming the platform, for the whole world to openly discuss, share, and launch programs for sustainable peace, or rather a culture with NO DISCRIMINATION, NO HATE, NO VIOLENCE, setting the past aside.  </p>
            <p>
              Today, OPF stands tall as a humanistic organization that reflects community outreach programs and has the potential to carve out better places to live in. These programs successfully empower families, assist social unity, efficiently build models of development and proactively promote moral and innovative leadership to the core. The organization leaves no stone unturned in embracing community, regional, national, and international peace building models thereby laying the foundation for the ethical and cohesive environment.
            </p>
            <p>OPF is robustly dedicated towards preventing any and every kind of violence. </p>
